{
  "texts": [
    "The real-space weight of the central band wavefunctions is concentrated around the AA regions.As noted previously, a key dimensionless parameter is the chiral ratio κ = w AA /w AB.",
    "Its precise value in experiments is debatable, but is expected to lie in the range 0.5 < κ < 0.8 [133,[148][149][150].",
    "Interactions have been argued to renormalize this down further [151].",
    "[152], this was taken to the extreme by setting κ = 0.",
    "In this so-called chiral limit, the model acquires a particle-hole symmetric spectrum due to the chiral symmetry { ĤBM, σ z } = 0."
  ]
}